      • DATE_PATTERN

        static final String DATE_PATTERN
        The regular expression pattern for parsing dates. All fields come in two versions - long and short form, the long form is for formats containing dashes, the short form is for formats without dashes. The long format is the only one that handles signed years, since that is how the only case that supports years with other than 4 numbers, and not having dashes then would make the format ambiguous. In order to not have two cases that can parse only the year, we let the long case handle that.

        Valid formats:

        • Year:
          • [0-9]{4} - unique without dashes, since it is the only one 4 numbers long
            Parsing: longYear
          • [+-] [0-9]{1,9}
            Parsing: longYear
        • Year & Month:
          • [0-9]{4} [0-9]{2} - unique without dashes, since it is the only one 6 numbers long
            Parsing: shortYear, shortMonth
          • [0-9]{4} - [0-9]{1,2}
            Parsing: longYear, longMonth
          • [+-] [0-9]{1,9} - [0-9]{1,2}
            Parsing: longYear, longMonth
        • Calendar date (Year & Month & Day):
          • [0-9]{4} [0-9]{2} [0-9]{2} - unique without dashes, since it is the only one 8 numbers long
            Parsing: shortYear, shortMonth, shortDay
          • [0-9]{4} - [0-9]{1,2} - [0-9]{1,2}
            Parsing: longYear, longMonth, longDay
          • [+-] [0-9]{1,9} - [0-9]{1,2} - [0-9]{1,2}
            Parsing: longYear, longMonth, longDay
        • Year & Week:
          • [0-9]{4} W [0-9]{2}
            Parsing: shortYear, shortWeek
          • [0-9]{4} - W [0-9]{2}
            Parsing: longYear, longWeek
          • [+-] [0-9]{1,9} - W [0-9]{2}
            Parsing: longYear, longWeek
        • Week date (year & week & day of week):
          • [0-9]{4} W [0-9]{2} [0-9] - unique without dashes, contains W followed by 2 numbers
            Parsing: shortYear, shortWeek, shortDOW
          • [0-9]{4} - W [0-9]{1,2} - [0-9]
            Parsing: longYear, longWeek, longDOW
          • [+-] [0-9]{1,9} - W [0-9]{2} - [0-9]
            Parsing: longYear, longWeek, longDOW
        • Ordinal date (year & day of year):
          • [0-9]{4} [0-9]{3} - unique without dashes, since it is the only one 7 number long
            Parsing: shortYear, shortDOY
          • [0-9]{4} - [0-9]{3} - needs to be exactly 3 numbers long to distinguish from Year & Month
            Parsing: longYear, longDOY
          • [+-] [0-9]{1,9} - [0-9]{3} - needs to be exactly 3 numbers long to distinguish from Year & Month
            Parsing: longYear, longDOY

      • parseDate

        static LocalDate parseDate​(Matcher matcher)
        Creates a LocalDate from a Matcher that matches the regular expression defined by DATE_PATTERN. The decision tree in the implementation of this method is guided by the parsing notes for DATE_PATTERN.
        Parameters:
        matcher - a Matcher that matches the regular expression defined in DATE_PATTERN.
        Returns:
        a LocalDate parsed from the given Matcher.
